WHAT IT DOES
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ansible-doc -l

Lists ALL available ansible modules installed
on your control node

output looks like:
  amazon.aws.aws_az_facts           Gather facts about ec2
  amazon.aws.ec2_instance           Create EC2 instances
  ansible.builtin.apt               Manages apt packages
  ansible.builtin.command           Execute commands
  ansible.builtin.copy              Copy files to remote
  ansible.builtin.file              Manage files
  ansible.builtin.ping              Try to connect to host
  ansible.builtin.shell             Execute shell commands
  ansible.builtin.yum               Manages packages with yum
  ... (thousands of modules)


USEFUL ansible-doc COMMANDS
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ansible-doc -l                    → list all modules
ansible-doc -l | wc -l            → count total modules
ansible-doc -l | grep aws         → filter aws modules only
ansible-doc -l | grep docker      → filter docker modules
ansible-doc -l | grep yum         → find yum related modules

ansible-doc yum                   → full docs for yum module
ansible-doc copy                  → full docs for copy module
ansible-doc shell                 → full docs for shell module

ansible-doc -s yum                → short snippet / example only
ansible-doc -s copy               → short snippet for copy
ansible-doc -s shell              → short snippet for shell


EXAMPLE OUTPUT OF ansible-doc yum
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

> YUM    (/usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/ansible/modules/yum.py)

  Installs, upgrade, downgrades, removes, and lists
  packages and groups with the yum package manager.

OPTIONS:
  name        → package name (required)
  state       → present / absent / latest
  update_cache→ update yum cache before install


EXAMPLE OUTPUT OF ansible-doc -s copy
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- name: task name
  copy:
    src:          # local path
    dest:         # remote path
    owner:        # file owner
    group:        # file group
    mode:         # permissions eg 0644
    backup:       # yes/no backup before overwrite


WHY IT IS USEFUL
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

→ no internet needed
→ works offline on server
→ shows exact parameter names
→ shows examples ready to copy
→ faster than googling


